FBIS3-58735 "drweu012__a94018" FBIS-WEU-94-012 Document Type:Daily Report 19 January 1994 ANNEX Germany Government Grants To East To Decrease in 1994 LD1301170994 Hamburg DPA in German 1055 GMT 13 Jan 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY LD1301170994 Hamburg DPA Language: German Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- After three years of rising government grants and subsidies from western to eastern Germany, 1994 will for the first time show a reduction in comparison with the previous year. In response to a query from DDP/ADN, the Finance Ministry revealed in Bonn on Thursday [13 January] that a total of 138 billion German marks [DM] was transferred to eastern Germany last year. In 1994, this sum will fall by DM5 billion to DM133 billion net (DM175 billion gross). [passage omitted] In 1991, DM107 billion net was made available for eastern Germany. In 1992, this sum rose to DM115 billion and was increased again last year by DM23 billion, according to official figures. That was the highest level of payments since German unification.
